subSubSection.paragraph:
Gnathosoma (
Figs. 2a, 2b
) — Subcapitulum anarthric, imperfectly protected by the rostral tectum when retracted, with pantelebasic rutella (
Grandjean 1957
), elongated without teeth, rectangular, forming distally elongated laminae with dorsal deep notch, ventrodistal angle with a small notch; chelicerae elongated with both movable and fixed digits, each with two sharply hooked teeth, incurvation opposed between digits, tightly locking at rest (
Fig. 2a
).
